Fix HTML rendering bug in Pipeline kanban cards

Root cause: multiline f-strings in st.markdown(unsafe_allow_html=True)
cause Streamlit's markdown parser to escape HTML tags that appear at the
start of a new line (e.g. </div>, <span class="pill">), displaying them
as literal text instead of rendering them.

Fixes applied:
- Added `import html as _html` at the top of app.py
- Kanban card HTML rebuilt as a single-line concatenated string (no
  multiline f-string) so no tag ever appears at line-start
- All user-provided values (sub['name'], sub['id'], sub['status']) now
  passed through _html.escape() before interpolation
- Kanban column header also converted to single-line concatenation with
  _html.escape() on stage name

Files changed: app.py
